SIMPLE: enjoy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enjoy
<hw>En*joy"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Enjoyed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Enjoying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>enjoier</ets> to
receive with joy; pref. <ets>en-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + OF. & F.
<ets>joie</ets> joy: cf. OF. <ets>enjoir</ets> to enjoy. See
<er>Joy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take pleasure or satisfaction
in the possession or experience of; to feel or perceive with pleasure;
to be delighted with; <as>as, to <ex>enjoy</ex> the dainties of a feast;
to <ex>enjoy</ex> conversation.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have, possess, and use with satisfaction; to
occupy or have the benefit of, as a good or profitable thing, or as
something desirable; <as>as, to <ex>enjoy</ex> a free constitution and
religious liberty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That the children of Israel may <qex>enjoy</qex> every man the
inheritance of his fathers.</q> <rj><qau>Num. xxxvi. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>enjoy</qex> the pleasures of sin for a season.</q>
<rj><qau>Heb. xi. 25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To have sexual intercourse with.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To enjoy one's self</b></col>, <cd>to feel pleasure; to
be happy.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enjoy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enjoy
<hw>En*joy"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To take satisfaction; to live in
happiness.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enjoyable</ent>⟦br⟧
